Timing_Desc.Sequence: Packet are in Sequence i.e, SS , ID ,CFG,CE, RP-8
Timing_Desc.twake: Object detected to start time of Signal Strength Packet +5.5ms
Timing_Desc.tstart: End of signal strength packet to start time of the identification packet +5.5ms
Timing_Desc.tstart_CNF: End of CNF ACK to start of FOD status packet
Timing_Desc.tsilent: End of signal strength packet to start time of the identification packet
Timing_Desc.tresponse: end of Configuration packet to start time of the configuration ACK packet
Timing_Desc.tintervalCNF-CE: Start time of Configuration packet  to Start time of first control error packet
Timing_Desc.tintervalCE-CE_PT: Start time of a control error packet  to start time of next control error packet in PT phase
Timing_Desc.tintervalCE-EPT: Start time of first CE packet to the start time of EPT packet
Timing_Desc.tintervalCE-SS: Start time of first CE packet to the Start time of Signal strength packet
Timing_Desc.tintervalCE-CHS: Start time of first CE packet to the Start time of CHS data packet packet
Timing_Desc.tintervalCE-PROP: Start time of first CE packet to the Start time of PROP data packet packet
Timing_Desc.tintervalCE-Reserved: Start time of first CE packet to the Start time of Reserved data packet packet
Timing_Desc.tintervalCE-CE_CL: Start time of First CE packet to start time of the next CE packet in Calib Phase
Timing_Desc.treceviedCNF-RP: Start time of configuration packet to start time of Received power packet
Timing_Desc.treceviedRP-RP_PT: Start time of Received power packet to next start time of 8bit Received power packet in PT phase
Timing_Desc.treceviedSRQ-RPM1: Start time of End Negotiation packet to start time of next  RP MODE 1 packet
Timing_Desc.treceviedRPM1-RPM2: Start time of RP MODE 1 packet to start time of RP MODE 2 packet
Timing_Desc.treceviedRPM2-RPM2: Start time of first RP MODE 2 packet to start time of next RP MODE 2 packet
Timing_Desc.treceviedRPM2-RPM0: Start time of  RP MODE 2 packet to start time of  RP MODE 0 packet
Timing_Desc.treceviedRPM0-RPM0: Start time of first RP MODE 0 packet to start time of next  RP MODE 0 packet
Timing_Desc.trecevied_PT: Time difference of 2 RP packet in the PT phase
Timing_Desc.CountCELoads: Verify at least ten CE data packets containing Control Error Values of –1, 0, or 1 before each step.
Timing_Desc.PCH_value: Power Control Hold of Value Check
Timing_Desc.RPM0-ADC: End of RP/0 to Start of ADC
Timing_Desc.ADC-ADT: Start of ADC packet to start of ADT packet
Timing_Desc.ADT-ADT: Start of First ADT packet to start of second ADT packet
Timing_Desc.ADT-ADC: Start of ADT packet to start ADC packet
Timing_Desc.ATN-DSR: end of ANT response to start of DSR packet
Timing_Desc.DSR-DSR: start of first DSR packet to the start of next DSR packet
Timing_Desc.RP0-Challenge: end of first RP0 to Challange response
Timing_Desc.Challenge-challangeAuth: End of challange to challange auth response
Timing_Desc.ADC-Chellange: End of ADC of preceding authentication  to Start of Challenge msg
Timing_Desc.Challange-ChallangeAuth: End of Challenge to Challenge auth response(Timing will vary based on number of bytes)
Timing_Desc.tintervalXCE-XCE: Start time of a control error packet  to start time of next control error packet in PT phase
Timing_Desc.treceviedPLA-PLA: Start time of PLA packet to next start time of PLA packet in PT phase

Measure_Desc.Vr1: The Load voltage UL (V1) measured at t1 = (44~46)ms after CE/+60
Measure_Desc.Vr2: The Load voltage UL (v2) measured at t2 = (74~76)ms after CE/+60
Measure_Desc.Vr3: The Load voltage UL (V3) measured at t3 = (104~106)ms after CE/+60
Measure_Desc.Vrmin: The Minimum Load voltage UL received between V1 and V2
Measure_Desc.Vrmax: ThemAximum Load voltage UL received between V1 and V2
Measure_Desc.UL: The Load voltage UL does not exceed specified Voltage in the final step of the test procedure
Measure_Desc.Fop: The frequency fop of the AC signal
Measure_Desc.tterminate: end of the last transmitted EPT data packet until the coil voltage uro drops below the 200 mV (pk-pk) level
Measure_Desc.tnextping: end of the last transmitted EPT data packet until the coil voltage uro raise above the 4 V (pk-pk) level
Measure_Desc.ADC_Response: Check Response for the ADC packet
Measure_Desc.ADT_Response: Check Response for the ADT packets
Measure_Desc.ttotal: Measure the time interval tnegotiate + tterminate from the end of the ACK Response Pattern to the CFG/ep data packet until the voltage uro drops below the 200 mV (pk-pk) level
Measure_Desc.tnopower: from uro dropping below the 200 mV (pk-pk) level for the first time after ceasing to send data packets, until uro ≥ 4 V (pk-pk) level.
Measure_Desc.T_total: end of the ACK Response Pattern to the CFG/ep data packet until the voltage uro drops below the 200 mV (pk-pk) level.

Other_Checks.PCH_val: To check that the PCH packet received between ID and CNF with specified value
Other_Checks.CE0Count: To check count of CE0 packets before and after CE60
Other_Checks.CEPCount: To Check specified no.of Positive CE packets received in sequnce during the Test
Other_Checks.CESCount: To Check specified no.of CE/-1/0/1 packets received in sequnce during the Test
Other_Checks.CHS_count: Number of CHS packet received during the Test
